## The Good
I've been expirimenting with guix home for a little while in a strive to have a less brittle
setup. It's overall been quite a pleasant expirience and I created a little [sample configuration](https://github.com/kyserd/guix-home-example)
that makes it easy to bootstrap home on a new install.

It's overall quite simple and with the help of guix shell has made it easy to self bootstrap.
I can use configuratio tools like `stow` and `just` to make managing the install easier without
having to create a seperate process for bootstrapping said tools. As soon as I can activate the pinned
guix binary I can create temporary shells containing the exact versions of `stow` and `just` my system
needs and then can use my already existing justfile to bootstrap the rest.

