## The Ugly
The bootstrapping in my opinion is super neat and I'd love to use this on my setups, but I've run into an issue which is
unfortunatly a bit of a deal breaker. Guix is slow. Not slow to the point where I can't use it, but it takes longer to install then the
OS itself. This is exacerbated by the fact that Guix 1.4.0, the latest release of Guix at the moment, doesn't support git redirects.
Guix transitioned from Savannah to Codeberg this year and that greatly improved the useability. But since redirects aren't supported,
one must update from Savannah first, which is unbearably slow.

There was a [consensus](https://consensus.guix.gnu.org/gcd/005-regular-releases.html) reached within Guix to start with
regular releases, which should hopefully solve or at least improve the speed problem. But until that happends, the dream
of having a quick and reproducible setup I can use in VM's or on real hardware with Guix Home is dead.

I don't plan to
abandon Guix forever, but for the moment I will be investigating alternatives as I don't want to wait 10-15 minutes just to
have 7 programs be installed and setup (especially if this is a one-shot VM instance).
